22.222144439466348},"alwaysFullscreen":false,"content":[{"params":{"text":"<p>Make sure to be looking at publishers. Google scholar pulls its results from the Open Access internet and our library catalog. This means that you should evaluate the results more critically. Click the journal title to learn more about the publication. You should look for their peer review process.&nbsp;<\/p>"},"library":"H5P.Text 1.1","metadata":{"contentType":"Text","license":"U","title":"Untitled Text"},"subContentId":"cb6b587c-0256-4581-a17f-a37bb7b9df71"}]},{"position":{"x":44,"y":22.63030945091597},"alwaysFullscreen":false,"content":[{"params":{"text":"<p>Pay attention to when articles were published. Do not use anything older than 25 years unless you are doing a historical study. The new standard since covid has been nothing older than 5 years. The newer the better!<\/p>"},"library":"H5P.Text 1.1","metadata":{"contentType":"Text","license":"U","title":"Untitled Text"},"subContentId":"9649e691-e0fd-4d69-a4e4-a925b59dcce9"}]},{"position":{"x":13.200000000000001,"y":30.953647700119475},"alwaysFullscreen":false,"content":[{"params":{"text":"<p>Google Scholar has a \"Save\" feature. You can save these articles and come back to them to read later on your profile.&nbsp;<\/p>"},"library":"H5P.Text 1.1","metadata":{"contentType":"Text","license":"U","title":"Untitled Text"},"subContentId":"54177146-587c-4f8f-bc01-fa96ecdbc52f"}]},{"position":{"x":18.8,"y":30.14742943548387},"alwaysFullscreen":false,"content":[{"params":{"text":"<p>Google Scholar has a citation function. Make sure to always check automatically generated citations. You can also export citations into RIS format to import into citation managers such as Zotero<\/p>"},"library":"H5P.Text 1.1","metadata":{"contentType":"Text","license":"U","title":"Untitled Text"},"subContentId":"fef99f32-0761-442d-b420-93d4d84ac75a"}]},{"position":{"x":72.8,"y":19.354683144165673},"alwaysFullscreen":false,"content":[{"params":{"text":"<p>This PDF link is to access the article. Notice how it says \"<em>Find it at North Central<\/em>\". This means it is avaliable to you via the North Central University Library Catalog. Simply click on the link to start reading.&nbsp;<\/p>"},"library":"H5P.Text 1.1","metadata":{"contentType":"Text","license":"U","title":"Untitled Text"},"subContentId":"d7456be0-ec44-4cf8-8eff-8254c85d3aee"}]},{"position":{"x":73.6,"y":53.962564715252896},"alwaysFullscreen":false,"content":[{"params":{"text":"<p>This PDF link is to access the article. Notice how it <strong>does not<\/strong> say \"<em>Find it at North Central<\/em>\". This means it was pulled from the Open Access Internet. This does <strong>not <\/strong>mean the article is not scholarly, it just means you should evaluate it critically. Click on the link to view the article<\/p>"},"library":"H5P.Text 1.1","metadata":{"contentType":"Text","license":"U","title":"Untitled Text"},"subContentId":"fae43b4d-b9b4-4876-82a0-fd4179f37381"}]},{"position":{"x":66,"y":88.09208233771406},"alwaysFullscreen":false,"content":[{"params":{"text":"<p>You may notice that some articles are missing the PDF link to access the article. This does <strong>not <\/strong>mean you do not have access to the article. It means that you will just have to submit an InterLibrary Loan Request to access it. To submit a request, go to library.northcentral.edu and submit a request. If you need more help with this, feel free to checkout our guide or contact the library for help library@northcentral.edu.<\/p>"},"library":"H5P.Text 1.1","metadata":{"contentType":"Text","license":"U","title":"Untitled Text"},"subContentId":"351f013e-47df-4300-956a-e4c49758e684"}]},{"position":{"x":89.60000000000001,"y":9.757068896853843},"alwaysFullscreen":false,"content":[{"params":{"text":"<p>To view your saved items, click on the star icon labed \"My Library\"<\/p>"},"library":"H5P.Text 1.1","metadata":{"contentType":"Text","license":"U","title":"Untitled Text"},"subContentId":"523108e